; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
; AutoUpdate.config.ini — template
; Copy this file to AutoUpdate.config.ini (same directory) and fill in the
; token. The real AutoUpdate.config.ini is .gitignore'd and must never be
; committed — it contains a GitHub Personal Access Token.
; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════
;
; Required PAT scope:
;   Fine-grained PAT with `Contents: Read` access to LightAISolutions/lightaisolutions.
;   The PAT already used by the Google Apps Script changelog-reader flow
;   (stored in each GAS project's Script Properties) has the same scope and
;   may be reused here — one PAT to rotate instead of two.
;
; Rotation guidance:
;   The token sits in plaintext on your-workstation. This is acceptable for an
;   internal server, but the PAT must be minimum-privilege (Contents: Read
;   only) and rotated immediately if the server is ever compromised.
;
; Deployment:
;   1. On your-workstation, copy this file to AutoUpdate.config.ini
;   2. Paste your PAT into the `token = ` line below
;   3. Save and launch AutoUpdate.ahk — the startup shortcut installs itself
;      on first run, and subsequent logons autostart the updater.
; ═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

[github]
token = github_pat_REPLACE_WITH_YOUR_TOKEN

; Developed by: ShadowAISolutions
